{"action": "input", "code": "def find_yellow_pattern(grid: np.ndarray, blue_pattern: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array representing a grid of colored blocks and a binary mask of the largest connected area of blue blocks,\n    returns a binary mask where True indicates the yellow blocks that have the same positional relationship with the yellow blocks in the blue area.\n    \n    Args:\n    - grid: a 2D numpy array of integers representing the color of each block\n    - blue_pattern: a 2D numpy array of booleans representing the binary mask of the largest connected area of blue blocks.\n    \n    Returns:\n    - A 2D numpy array of booleans representing the binary mask of the yellow blocks that have the same positional relationship with the yellow blocks in the blue area.\n    \"\"\"\n    yellow_pattern = np.zeros_like(grid, dtype=bool)\n    yellow_pattern[grid == yellow] = True\n    blue_indices = np.argwhere(blue_pattern)\n    yellow_indices = np.argwhere(yellow_pattern)\n    for i, j in yellow_indices:\n        if all(((i + x, j + y) in blue_indices for x, y in ((-1, 0), (1, 0), (0, -1), (0, 1)))):\n            yellow_pattern[i, j] = True\n    return yellow_pattern\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    pattern = find_largest_blue_area(input_grid)\n    out = find_yellow_pattern(input_grid, pattern)\n    return out\ndef find_largest_blue_area(grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array representing a grid of colored blocks, returns a binary mask\n    where True indicates the largest connected area of blue blocks.\n    \n    Args:\n    - grid: a 2D numpy array of integers representing the color of each block\n    \n    Returns:\n    - A 2D numpy array of booleans representing the binary mask of the largest connected area of blue blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    pattern = _find_blue_pattern(grid)\n    out = _find_largest_connected_area(grid, pattern)\n    return out", "user_code": "def main(input_gr